entation": ["This function registers the font file using `fontconfig` so that\nit is available for use by Pango. On Linux it is aliased to\n{func}`register_font` and on Windows and macOS this would work only when\nusing `fontconfig` backend.\n\n# Parameters\n\nfont_path\n\n: Relative or absolute path to font file.\n\n# Returns\n\n{class}`bool`\n\n: True means it worked without any error.\n  False means there was an unknown error\n\n# Examples\n\n```pycon\n>>> register_font(\"/home/roboto.tff\")\nTrue\n```\n\n# Raises\n\nAssertionError\n\n: The {param}`font_path` specified doesn't exist.\n"]}, {"name": "manimpango.register_font.fc_unregister_font", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "font_path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["This function unregister (removes) the font file using\n`fontconfig`. It is mostly optional to call this.\nMainly used in tests. On Linux it is aliased to\n{func}`unregister_font` and on Windows and macOS this\nwould work only when using `fontconfig` backend.\n\n# Parameters\n\nfont_path: {class}`str`\n\n: For compatibility with the windows function.\n\n# Returns\n\n{class}`bool`\n\n: True means it worked without any error.\n  False means there was an unknown error\n"]}, {"name": "manimpango.register_font.register_font", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "font_path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["This function registers the font file using native OS API\nto make the font available for use by Pango. On Linux it is\naliased to {func}`fc_register_font` and on Windows and macOS\nit uses the native API.\n\n# Parameters\n\nfont_path: {class}`str`\n\n: Relative or absolute path to font file.\n\n# Returns\n\n{class}`bool`\n\n: True means it worked without any error.\n  False means there was an unknown error\n\n# Examples\n\n```pycon\n>>> register_font(\"C:/home/roboto.tff\")\nTrue\n```\n\n# Raises\n\nAssertionError\n\n: The {param}`font_path` specified doesn't exist.\n"]}, {"name": "manimpango.register_font.unregister_font", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "font_path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["This function unregister (removes) the font file using native OS API.\nIt is mostly optional to call this. Mainly used in tests. On Linux it is\naliased to {func}`fc_unregister_font` and on Windows and macOS it uses\nthe native API.\n\n# Parameters\n\nfont_path: {class}`str`\n\n: Relative or absolute path to font file.\n\n# Returns\n\n{class}`bool`\n\n: True means it worked without any error.\n  False means there was an unknown error\n\n# Examples\n\n```pycon\n>>> unregister_font(\"C:/home/roboto.tff\")\nTrue\n```\n\n# Raises\n\nAssertionError\n\n: The {param}`font_path` specified doesn't exist.\n"]}, {"name": "manimpango.register_font.list_fonts", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Lists the fonts available to Pango.\nThis is usually same as system fonts but it also\nincludes the fonts added through {func}`register_font`\nor {func}`fc_register_font`.\n\n# Returns\n\n{class}`list` :\n\n: List of fonts sorted alphabetically.\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "manimpango.register_font.registered_fonts", "type": {"name": "set", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.set", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "RegisteredFont", "xref": {"fqname": "manimpa